    {
      "step_id": "3b853c4b",
      "step_index": 2,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "**Key structural elements**\n- **Two amide groups**:  \n  - `CC(=O)N\u2013(tetralin)` and `\u2013N C(=O)\u2013(aniline)`  \n  Amides are **not basic** (lone pair delocalized), but are strong H-bond acceptor/donor motifs and add polarity.\n- **Amidine-like / hydrazone motif**: `C/C(...)=N\\N C(=O)...`  \n  This is a **conjugated imine (C=N) adjacent to an \u2013NH\u2013 that is acylated** (i.e., a semicarbazone-like fragment). The **imine N is weakly basic at best** due to conjugation with carbonyl(s); the adjacent N is an **amide N (non-basic)**.\n- **Aromatic/hydrophobic ring systems**\n  - **Tetralin (benzocyclohexane)**: `c1cccc2c1CCCC2` \u2192 bulky, lipophilic, aromatic + fused saturated ring.\n  - **Phenyl ring with an aniline \u2013NH2**: `c1ccccc1N` \u2192 aromatic and provides an H-bond donor; aniline is **weakly basic** (pKaH typically ~4\u20136, often largely neutral at pH 7.4 depending on substitution).",
      "tool_name": null,
      "tool_input": null,
      "tool_output": null,
      "timestamp": "2026-02-26T19:47:29.533591+00:00"
    },
    {
      "step_id": "7a2dd2d7",
      "step_index": 3,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "**Structural alerts relevant to CYP2D6 inhibition**\n- Has **lipophilic aromatic rings** (good for CYP2D6 binding).\n- **Lacks a clear, strongly protonatable tertiary amine** (a common hallmark of potent CYP2D6 inhibitors like quinidine/paroxetine/fluoxetine).\n- Contains **multiple H-bond donors/acceptors** (amide NHs, aniline NH2, imine N), which can support binding but also increase polarity and may reduce the \u201ccationic anchor\u201d interaction typical for CYP2D6 inhibitors.",
      "tool_name": null,
      "tool_input": null,
      "tool_output": null,
      "timestamp": "2026-02-26T19:47:29.533604+00:00"
    },
    {
      "step_id": "08709154",
      "step_index": 4,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "## 2) SAR reasoning (why these features matter for CYP2D6 inhibition)",
      "tool_name": null,
      "tool_input": null,
      "tool_output": null,
